<Layout title="Shinobi NVR: Open-Source CCTV Solution Based on Node.js — Rupadana">
  <article class="reveal">
    <span class="tag">Tools</span>
    <h1>Shinobi NVR: Open-Source CCTV Solution Based on Node.js</h1>
    <div class="meta">Building a lightweight, modern, and flexible self-hosted surveillance system.</div>

    <div class="card article-content">
      <p>
        If you are looking for an open-source alternative to manage your CCTV or IP cameras, <strong>Shinobi NVR</strong> is currently one of the best options. Unlike many traditional NVR systems that feel heavy and rigid, Shinobi is built using <strong>Node.js</strong> and focuses on performance and ease of use for developers.
      </p>

      <div class="callout">
        Shinobi is an open-source Network Video Recorder (NVR) designed to be lightweight yet feature-rich for both home and business security needs.
      </div>

      <h2>Why Choose Shinobi?</h2>
      <p>
        Shinobi offers several key advantages over competitors like ZoneMinder or proprietary vendor NVR systems:
      </p>
      
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Modern Architecture:</strong> Using Node.js and FFmpeg, Shinobi handles video streams efficiently.</li>
        <li><strong>Lightweight & Fast:</strong> It doesn't require as many resources as older NVR systems, making it suitable for small servers or VPS environments.</li>
        <li><strong>Multi-Protocol Support:</strong> Supports RTSP, RTMP, HTTP, ONVIF, and more.</li>
        <li><strong>Responsive Web Interface:</strong> Allows for control and monitoring directly from the browser without needing additional plugins.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Key Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Time-Lapse & Recording:</strong> Record video in modern formats like MP4 or WebM.</li>
        <li><strong>Motion Detection:</strong> Software-based motion detection or integration with AI plugins (such as Object Detection).</li>
        <li><strong>Cloud Storage Support:</strong> Ability to upload recordings to cloud storage or remote servers via FTP/SFTP.</li>
        <li><strong>API First:</strong> Easily integrated into home automation systems or custom applications through a comprehensive API.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Installation (The Ninja Way)</h2>
      <p>
        Shinobi provides a very easy installation script for Linux (Ubuntu/Debian). Just run this one-line command in your terminal:
      </p>

      <pre><code>bash <(curl -s https://cdn.shinobi.video/installers/shinobi-install.sh)</code></pre>

      <p>
        This script will automatically install dependencies like Node.js, FFmpeg, and MariaDB, and configure Shinobi so it's ready to use.
      </p>

      <h2>Conclusion</h2>
      <p>
        Shinobi NVR is the right choice for anyone who wants full control over their security system without expensive licensing fees. With active community support and fast development, Shinobi proves that professional-grade security systems can be built on modern open-source technology.
      </p>

      <p>
        Are you ready to turn your old PC or server into a smart surveillance hub? <em>Shinobi is the way.</em>
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

